videos.description: Kentucky battles on the offensive glass, and Keldon Johnson finishes the play with a layup.

videos.headline: Johnson takes advantage of Kentucky's third chance

videos.description: Dedric Lawson buries the 3-pointer, which extends Kansas' run to 10-0.

videos.headline: Dedric Lawson forces timeout from a frustrated Calipari

videos.description: Ashton Hagans intercepts Quentin Grimes' pass and runs the floor before bouncing an assist to Reid Travis for the hoop and the harm.

videos.headline: Hagans' steal sets up Travis' and-1 layup

videos.description: Reid Travis pulls down an offensive rebound in a sea of opposing blue jerseys, then absorbs contact to hit the and-1 lay-in.
videos.headline: Travis mean-mugs after impressive layup

videos.description: Kentucky takes its largest lead of the game after Keldon Johnson sinks the corner 3-pointer forcing a Kansas timeout.

videos.headline: Rupp Arena erupts after Johnson's corner 3

videos.description: Tyler Herro and PJ Washington run the perfect pick and roll, as Herro hits Washington for the easy dunk.

videos.headline: Herro and Washington play the 2-man game to perfection

videos.description: PJ Washington, Reid Travis and Keldon Johnson all register double-doubles as the No. 8 Wildcats knock off the No. 9 Jayhawks 71-63.
